comment: If the metric ` D ` is "strongly finer" than ` C ` (meaning that there is a positive real constant ` R ` such that ` C ( x , y ) <_ R x. D ( x , y ) ` ), all the ` D ` -Cauchy sequences are also ` C ` -Cauchy. (Using this theorem twice in each direction states that if two metrics are strongly equivalent, then they have the same Cauchy sequences.) (Contributed by Mario Carneiro, 14-Sep-2015.)
